commitResults.messageTitle: Implement skeleton for edit appointment command
commitResults.messageBody: Add parser and placeholder logic for the edit appointment command. Placeholder logic uses index of a patient in the list instead of the actual patient, and the parser parses the index instead of ID. It requires the model to be passed from LogicManager to AddressBookParser for now. This will be removed once patient ID is implemented.

commitResults.messageTitle: Store appointment list in memory and fix tests
Implement list and edit appointment commands
commitResults.messageBody:
Add `list_appt` command to list all appointments. Since appointments are not implemented in the GUI yet, the list of appointments will be output in the terminal instead.

Add `edit_appt` command to edit an appointment. Appointment IDs are shared with patient IDs so the first appointment ID will be the lowest unused integer after all the patient IDs have been initialised. In the sample data, this will be 7. References to the patient using patient ID has not been fully implemented yet, so the patient ID might change to an arbitrary number for now.
